          <p class=3D"post-summary">Impatience has a cost: unrecoverable in=
stall!</p>        <h1 class=3D"post-title">Why You Shouldn=E2=80=99t Upgrad=
e to Ubuntu 24.04 LTS Yet</h1>
                      <div class=3D"post-meta">
                <img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/262=
3034032315d5cf0bcf5e213ff5547?s=3D36&amp;d=3Dretro&amp;r=3Dg" class=3D"avat=
ar avatar-36 photo post-author__avatar" height=3D"36" width=3D"36" decoding=
=3D"async">              <a class=3D"post-author" href=3D"https://www.omgub=
untu.co.uk/author/d0od" title=3D"View all posts by Joey Sneddon">
                <span class=3D"post-by">by</span> Joey Sneddon             =
 </a>
              <span class=3D"post-meta__divider">=C2=B7</span>
                                  <span class=3D"post-updated">
                            Updated <time class=3D"post-updated" datetime=
=3D"28 Apr 2024" title=3D"Published on 26 Apr 2024. Updated on 28 Apr 2024 =
at 11:56 PM Europe/London.">Sunday</time></span>
                                                  <span class=3D"post-meta_=
_divider">=C2=B7</span>
                  <a rel=3D"noamphtml" class=3D"omg-track-comment-count" hr=
ef=3D"https://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2024/04/dont-upgrade-to-ubuntu-24-04-yet#=
comments"><span class=3D"dsq-postid disqus-comment-count" data-talk-id=3D"2=
81688" data-disqus-identifier=3D"281688 https://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/?p=3D28=
1688">85 Comments</span>
                  </a>
                            </div>
                </header>
                            <div class=3D"entry-content post-content">
                        <div class=3D"wp-block-image is-style-rounded">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-large"><a href=3D"https://149366088.v2.pr=
essablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/dontupgradeyet.jpg"><img fetchpri=
ority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"840" height=3D"441" src=3D"https=
://149366088.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/dontupgradeyet-=
840x441.jpg" alt=3D"" class=3D"wp-image-281689"></a></figure></div>


<p><strong>With <a href=3D"https://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2024/04/ubuntu-24-04=
-released">Ubuntu 24.04 LTS released</a> and a long weekend upon us you mig=
ht be planning to upgrade an existing Ubuntu install to the latest version.=
</strong></p>



<p>But don=E2=80=99t.</p>



<p>For one, =E2=80=9Cofficially=E2=80=9D you can=E2=80=99t since<strong> Ub=
untu 24.04 LTS upgrades are not yet enabled</strong>, neither from Ubuntu 2=
3.10 nor 22.04 LTS. </p>



<p>But that doesn=E2=80=99t stop <s>us</s> folks from upgrading manually. <=
/p>



<p>They hear that a new version of Ubuntu is out and stable, they don=E2=80=
=99t fancy the faff of a fresh install, <em>and</em> they don=E2=80=99t wan=
t to wait for the =E2=80=9Cnew version available=E2=80=9D upgrade prompt to=
 appear on their desktop.</p>



<p>So they go to Google for a =E2=80=98how to=E2=80=99, learn about the <co=
de>sudo do-release-upgrade -d</code> command, run it, and away they go sayi=
ng to themselves:</p>



<p><em>=E2=80=9CThe final release is stable so upgrading, even with the -d =
flag should be safe!=E2=80=9D</em></p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image is-style-rounded">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full"><a href=3D"https://149366088.v2.pre=
ssablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/not-this-time.gif"><img decoding=
=3D"async" width=3D"840" height=3D"483" src=3D"https://149366088.v2.pressab=
lecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/not-this-time.gif" alt=3D"" class=3D"w=
p-image-281705"></a></figure></div>


<p>Right now there are major bugs impacting direct upgrades from earlier ve=
rsions.</p>



<p>We=E2=80=99re talking <em>=E2=80=9Cyour system may become unrecoverable=
=E2=80=9D</em> type issues.</p>



<p>Snafus stem from the switch to <em>Thunderbird</em> snap<sup data-fn=3D"=
94ddbde0-2633-42e6-8360-98e861b8650e" class=3D"fn"><a href=3D"https://www.o=
mgubuntu.co.uk/2024/04/dont-upgrade-to-ubuntu-24-04-yet#94ddbde0-2633-42e6-=
8360-98e861b8650e" id=3D"94ddbde0-2633-42e6-8360-98e861b8650e-link">1</a></=
sup> (on installs with the DEB installed upgrading to 24.04 replaces it wit=
h the snap) and the complicated tangle of Y2028 time_t transitions<sup data=
-fn=3D"1ffe46bc-7ba3-40b1-8e0c-ce8a6ecd546c" class=3D"fn"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2024/04/dont-upgrade-to-ubuntu-24-04-yet#1ffe46bc-7ba=
3-40b1-8e0c-ce8a6ecd546c" id=3D"1ffe46bc-7ba3-40b1-8e0c-ce8a6ecd546c-link">=
2</a></sup> (anyone who used daily builds will be familiar with the pain th=
ey caused). </p>



<p><strong>Critical fixes are on the way</strong> but until they arrive and=
 Ubuntu=E2=80=99s developers are able to re-test direct upgrades to verify =
they solve things (and don=E2=80=99t introduce further issues) official upg=
rades can=E2=80=99t be enabled <em>and</em> CLI DIY upgrades are strictly n=
ot advised.</p>



<p>As of writing this (before I depart for the weekend) those fixes aren=E2=
=80=99t in place. </p>



<p>My advice for now is to forget what blogs say =E2=80=94<em>stones, glass=
 houses, etc</em> =F0=9F=98=85=E2=80=94 and do not upgrade through any mean=
s until Ubuntu=E2=80=99s engineers give the nod. </p>



<p>Super-duper impatient? Suck it up and download the ISO and do a fresh in=
stall instead. Those are <strong>not</strong> affected by these issues and,=
 on the plus side, you get to see all the fancy new options added to the de=
sktop installer.</p>


