that are only found once it=E2=80=99s being used by non-testers, in specifi=
c sorts of setups, niche scenarios, once third party apps are updated to su=
pport the new release, and so on.</p><p>So it makes sense to kind of=E2=80=
=A6 =E2=80=9Cgate=E2=80=9D upgrades for a little longer so all of those thi=
ngs can be found, fixed, and so on.</p><p>Of course, 22.04 LTS users don=E2=
=80=99t have to wait until the first point release to upgrade. Once the upg=
rade is enabled for 23.10 it=E2=80=99s also possible to upgrade 22.04 by sw=
itching the setting in Software &amp; Updates to notify for =E2=80=9Cany ne=
w version=E2=80=9D instead of =E2=80=9Ca new LTS only=E2=80=9D to get it so=
oner.</p></div></div><span class=3D"post-media"><ul data-role=3D"post-media=
