<p>I did the upgrade on a few machines last week. The Ubuntu server ones ha=
d no problem (though I accidently cleared my samba config on one, but that =
wasn't too hard to fix).</p><p>I had one running lubuntu which also had no =
problem.</p><p>I have some that run kubuntu that have been dist upgraded fr=
om way back, and one of those got messed up so bad I thought I was going to=
 have to reinstall, but I used dpkg to force install libraries and remove p=
ackages I didn't care about until I got past the giant breakage list and th=
en installed kubuntu-desktop and ran apt dist upgrade plus the ubuntu-drive=
rs auto install again. It seemed like I had some multi arch library issues =
and maybe some issues with -dev packages hanging around causing breakages a=
cross the transition to t64 suffix packages.</p><p>I was able to avoid this=
 on my other kubuntu machines by proactively removing manually selected leg=
acy and obsolete packages and anything auto removable after that. It still =
didn't stop the upgrade from failing in the middle, but apt install -f got =
things to continue and then installing the *-desktop package followed by ap=
t dist upgrade and running Ubuntu driver's to double check that my video ca=
rd drivers were still installed.</p><p>If all that sounds like too much, th=
en wait on the upgrade. ;)</p></div></div><span class=3D"post-media"><ul da=
